WEBVTT

00:00.962 --> 00:02.224
Take this church, good morning.

00:02.324 --> 00:05.068
So glad that you're joining us again today.

00:05.268 --> 00:08.493
Okay, let's begin with this moment.

00:08.513 --> 00:13.180
Have you ever had the experience where you cannot find something and you know it's there?

00:13.981 --> 00:16.865
I think every single one of us have had this experience with ourselves.

00:17.146 --> 00:21.432
It's usually with a roommate or a spouse or a sibling.

00:21.492 --> 00:23.435
So I've shared this before.

00:23.595 --> 00:24.697
Maybe you've had this experience.

00:24.717 --> 00:25.738
I'm sitting in front of the fridge.

00:26.339 --> 00:27.100
I opened the fridge.

00:27.241 --> 00:28.282
I'm looking for the mustard.

00:28.462 --> 00:29.103
I move everything.

00:29.284 --> 00:30.866
I cannot find the mustard.

00:31.202 --> 00:35.490
And so I yell in my home to my wife, Joanna, I can't find the mustard.

00:35.570 --> 00:36.512
She's probably upstairs.

00:36.952 --> 00:38.074
She's like, what are you yelling?

00:38.134 --> 00:39.357
That I'm yelling, I need the mustard.

00:39.377 --> 00:40.519
She's like, I can't hear you.

00:40.879 --> 00:44.125
Probably we end up FaceTiming because that's how we do life in 2023.

00:44.546 --> 00:46.770
All that to say, I'm like, I cannot find the mustard.

00:47.202 --> 00:48.564
And she's like, John, it's in the fridge.

00:48.584 --> 00:49.945
And I'm like, no, it's not in the fridge.

00:49.965 --> 00:51.307
She's like, yes, it is in the fridge.

00:51.327 --> 00:53.750
I'm like, no, it's not in the fridge.

00:53.770 --> 00:55.152
She's like, have you moved things?

00:55.572 --> 00:56.533
Then, of course, get offended.

00:56.573 --> 00:58.235
Yes, I've moved everything.

00:58.276 --> 01:00.378
The world has been moved to find the mustard.

01:00.438 --> 01:01.379
I need the mustard.

01:02.220 --> 01:06.185
And she's like, if I come downstairs and I find the mustard, you know the moment.

01:06.205 --> 01:09.369
It moves from conversation to debate, to threat.

01:09.529 --> 01:10.130
Anyway,

01:10.242 --> 01:11.763
I said, I cannot find the mustard.

01:11.783 --> 01:13.945
And so I hear her coming down the stairs.

01:14.006 --> 01:17.249
And she walks into the kitchen, into the environment.

01:17.609 --> 01:19.931
And she gives you sort of that bombastic side eye.

01:19.971 --> 01:20.952
You know what I'm talking about.

01:20.972 --> 01:22.353
So I'm just sitting there.

01:22.433 --> 01:23.615
And she opens the fridge.

01:23.635 --> 01:25.276
And she's like, are you really?

01:25.296 --> 01:32.323
And of course, it's literally in front of my face right there.

01:32.743 --> 01:34.004
Everything else has moved.

01:34.285 --> 01:36.306
And the mustard's right there.

01:36.327 --> 01:37.548
And she's like, seriously.

01:37.608 --> 01:38.729
I'm like, I'm so sorry.

01:38.749 --> 01:40.050
And she's like, seriously.

01:40.130 --> 01:41.232
And then, of course, leaves.

01:42.253 --> 01:46.038
I think I have this unfortunate spiritual gift all the time of missing things.

01:46.239 --> 01:53.749
And I'm quite convinced that the spiritual gift of seeing what's not in front of you or not seeing what's in front of you is given to every single teenager.

01:53.769 --> 01:55.191
It must be genetics.

01:55.252 --> 01:58.977
This happens all the time, except when my teenagers cry, I cannot find it.

01:59.077 --> 02:00.739
They tend not to move anything either.

02:00.759 --> 02:03.383
They just think it magically will appear.

02:04.365 --> 02:08.210
This whole sermon today is about the mustard right in front of our faces.

02:08.834 --> 02:25.010
Either we can't see it, and it's right there, or we've seen it so much actually, we just look beside it or beyond it, even though it's the thing we need, or actually for some of us, it's the thing we're not interested in, we actually don't want mustard, we think we want something else, but it's actually what we need.

02:26.031 --> 02:37.362
Today, every time in September I stop, and I get up and I preach a sermon, which I keep preaching at least once or twice a year in some form, and

02:37.634 --> 02:40.018
Every year, I'm asked, why do you do the same thing?

02:40.058 --> 02:44.044
And I'm like, well, lots of new people joined us over the summer or last year.

02:44.084 --> 02:52.036
And this is a significant moment where it becomes clear for you who've joined us to understand either what church you've joined or what church you're checking out.

02:52.797 --> 02:57.584
For us who belong to this church and also those who have just joined, this is our yearly checkup.

02:57.664 --> 02:58.806
This is our yearly way.

02:58.866 --> 03:03.593
And this is the moment where we have an honest conversation with God ourselves and each other.

03:03.994 --> 03:06.898
How am I truly doing in my spiritual life?

03:07.842 --> 03:10.124
And the thing that we need to do that is the mustard.

03:10.144 --> 03:12.587
It's right in front of us, but we're so used to it either.

03:12.947 --> 03:13.908
We again can't see it.

03:14.148 --> 03:17.231
We look by it or we don't want it, but we all actually need this.

03:18.353 --> 03:20.334
So let me start where I did last week.

03:21.315 --> 03:22.717
Why does Sanctus Church exist?

03:23.277 --> 03:25.380
Why do we give, why do we do everything?

03:25.480 --> 03:30.164
Well, it's connected to our mission statement to glorify God.

03:30.405 --> 03:31.205
He's supreme.

03:31.225 --> 03:35.890
He's first enabling people of all ages and nations.

03:36.130 --> 03:38.238
to become fully devoted followers of Jesus Christ.

03:39.082 --> 03:44.242
And then every year, in September I asked this question, what do you mean by fully devoted?

03:44.770 --> 03:47.492
What does a fully devoted follower of Jesus look like?

03:47.532 --> 03:49.414
And of course, we're coming from different places.

03:49.454 --> 03:54.558
So some of you are seekers and skeptics, and you're not sure what any of this means.

03:54.639 --> 03:58.102
Some of you are brand new Christians, so you have no starting point at all.

03:58.582 --> 04:01.124
Others of us have been walking with Jesus for years.

04:01.424 --> 04:02.666
We have some key ideas.

04:02.786 --> 04:13.455
Tons of you have moved into areas where our church is, and you've joined us from another church, and they use different words for what we mean here, and that causes confusion as we're trying to do this all together.

04:13.855 --> 04:14.756
So we have worked

04:14.736 --> 04:17.740
hard and we unashamedly repeat this.

04:17.821 --> 04:24.570
So we will have a common script so we can keep walking together, moving together in the same direction with the same understanding.

04:25.031 --> 04:30.479
So personally in this church, we can follow the author and pioneer and perfecter of our faith, Jesus.

04:30.659 --> 04:32.302
Now, it's not going to head of ourselves.

04:32.602 --> 04:33.844
We need to stop and ask again.

04:33.904 --> 04:36.628
What's a follower of Jesus let alone fully devoted?

04:37.169 --> 04:40.975
And of course, many of you know this, the original name for us was not Christian.

04:41.015 --> 04:43.378
Christian actually was usually an insult.

04:43.554 --> 04:47.378
The phrase that was used all through the scriptures was disciple.

04:48.299 --> 04:50.521
Disciple, of course, is a churchy word now.

04:50.621 --> 04:51.742
It's an ancient word.

04:52.243 --> 04:57.488
And again, many of us who have done church for so long don't understand the implications of this.

04:57.548 --> 05:00.030
So every year I quote a guy named Ray Vanderlin.

05:00.090 --> 05:04.374
Now, as I do this again, I'm going to focus in on something I haven't done before.

05:05.055 --> 05:06.236
So this is what he writes.

05:06.777 --> 05:11.161
Like all rabbis of Jesus' day, Jesus had disciples.

05:11.181 --> 05:12.082
Incredibly common.

05:12.514 --> 05:19.944
The disciples deepest desire was to follow their rabbi so closely that they'd start to think like the rabbi and act like the rabbi.

05:20.044 --> 05:21.846
Okay, pause, pause, pause, pause.

05:22.867 --> 05:33.721
You've been taught, I've been taught, our whole culture screams at us that the most important thing you need to do in your life is think for yourself and act the way you think you should be.

05:34.522 --> 05:36.605
You do your own thinking, no one else should think for you.

05:36.645 --> 05:40.370
And by the way, life is fulfilled

05:40.770 --> 05:47.019
when you yourself act in a way that makes you feel free or good or fulfilled.

05:48.101 --> 05:55.492
And the Jewish understanding of religious formation is fundamentally against everything we take for granted in our culture.

05:56.313 --> 05:56.834
So ready?

05:56.914 --> 05:57.696
Let me do this again.

05:57.716 --> 06:07.250
They wanted to follow their rabbi so closely, they would start to think like him, not like yourself, and act like him, not what I want to think or act like.

06:07.714 --> 06:08.495
And then it keeps reading.

06:08.515 --> 06:14.161
They were devote followers, probably in their mid-teens, so a gifted student would approach a rabbi and say, may I follow you?

06:14.281 --> 06:17.865
In effect, the question is, do I have what it takes to be like you?

06:17.925 --> 06:22.590
And the rabbi would either say yes, and they become a disciple, or say no, and then they go and do a trade.

06:22.991 --> 06:26.675
So Jesus, this is, again, such hopeful truth.

06:26.715 --> 06:29.418
We miss by just reading the scriptures on the surface.

06:29.919 --> 06:32.642
Jesus broke this pattern when he chose his own disciples.

06:33.703 --> 06:35.325
He asked his disciples to follow him.

06:35.385 --> 06:36.626
They knew without a doubt

06:37.026 --> 06:38.969
that their rabbi now already believed in them.

06:39.950 --> 06:46.079
Now a disciple again would follow the rabbi everywhere without knowing or asking where he was even going.

06:47.481 --> 06:51.927
Rarely they'd leave the rabbi side because they were afraid they'd miss that amazing teachable moment.

06:52.228 --> 06:59.338
The disciples' deepest desire was to follow the rabbi so closely they'd think like him and they'd act like him.

06:59.458 --> 07:04.765
Or as Ray said in another place, they followed him so closely they wanted to be covered in his dust.

07:04.926 --> 07:05.266
Okay.

07:05.698 --> 07:27.178
So if we're going to follow Jesus so close and of our ultimate desire is to think like Jesus and act like Jesus and be covered in the dust of Jesus, then the question we need to ask is where can I find Jesus to know him, be like him, hear from him, be transformed by him in an ongoing way, since supposedly he's risen from the dead and alive.

07:28.399 --> 07:31.022
And then this is a phrase we've used for years here at Cactus.

07:31.502 --> 07:35.506
Are there guaranteed places of encounter where everyday ordinary people like us

07:35.970 --> 07:37.152
can actually encounter Jesus.

07:37.772 --> 07:43.360
So if I walk in certain environments, if I walk in certain places, if I do certain practices, can I always find Jesus?

07:44.141 --> 07:45.703
Is that a right expectation?

07:45.723 --> 07:50.029
Because remember, expectations can crush, destroy, or bring life.

07:50.890 --> 07:52.673
The answer, if you're a Christian, is yes.

07:53.093 --> 07:59.542
Though God is omnipresent, that is everywhere, according to the Bible, he comes very close and can be encountered.

08:00.684 --> 08:05.330
So this sets what I would call biblical, godly,

08:05.570 --> 08:07.272
appropriate expectation.

08:08.013 --> 08:17.242
And what I'm about to share, this truth transcends gender, age, education, transcends my preference, your preference on size of church or style of church.

08:17.282 --> 08:23.188
It goes beyond, do I like the worship style or who's preaching today or who's in charge or how they dress?

08:24.410 --> 08:28.634
I can say, as I'm about to do, this is true, this is guaranteed.

08:28.994 --> 08:30.576
And by the way, this changes everything.

08:30.876 --> 08:32.498
The size of church does not matter.

08:33.634 --> 08:35.576
who's more gifted in this case does not matter.

08:36.958 --> 08:38.900
Who has money in this case does not matter.

08:39.701 --> 08:50.072
How I'm feeling today, or what season of life I'm in, up down boring, exciting, though important, does not change this truth.

08:51.273 --> 08:57.921
It's like if you're in a house, and this is true of many of our houses, and you have like 100 gorgeous cookbooks, or 50, or 20, or 10.

08:58.341 --> 08:59.282
You have all these cookbooks.

08:59.650 --> 09:02.760
And they're beautiful and they're stunning and the photographs are amazing.

09:02.800 --> 09:06.351
The food looks incredible and they're beautifully designed and they look amazing on your shelf.

09:06.391 --> 09:13.554
But if you do not ever use them, then it makes you feel good that you have them, but you never actually do the thing.

09:13.794 --> 09:14.856
you're being invited into.

09:14.876 --> 09:15.637
It's like gym equipment.

09:15.657 --> 09:21.786
You can have it in your house, but if you do not use it, you might feel good because you see it, but it brings no change.

09:21.866 --> 09:22.908
This again is like the mustard.

09:22.928 --> 09:25.973
You need to reach in, see the mustard, and actually do it.

09:26.153 --> 09:35.247
So some of us have heard literally what I'm saying 20 times, but we never move beyond looking at the gym equipment, looking at the cookbooks, looking at the mustard.

09:36.509 --> 09:42.258
So the question is, ask this all the time, if I want to actually begin

09:42.402 --> 09:46.987
to be or continue to be transformed, where do I walk with Jesus?

09:47.267 --> 09:49.410
And I say there's all these guaranteed places of encounter.

09:49.430 --> 09:53.234
The very first one is actually the good news of Jesus himself.

09:53.955 --> 10:01.002
It's when the gospel, the good news about the life, death and resurrection of Jesus for the forgiveness of sins is proclaimed.

10:01.943 --> 10:03.505
Paul put it best in Romans chapter one.

10:03.525 --> 10:04.826
I'm not ashamed of the gospel.

10:05.607 --> 10:08.210
It has the power or it is the power

10:09.154 --> 10:12.880
of God for salvation, for whoever believes, first Jews, the non-Jews.

10:12.900 --> 10:17.668
Now the word powers where we get our word dynamite from, the gospel literally is alive.

10:18.590 --> 10:20.814
It has sheer dynamic life-giving power.

10:21.194 --> 10:25.842
It's where the Holy Spirit takes all the work of Jesus' work past present future.

10:25.954 --> 10:29.700
and God the Father's calling and puts it into a human being's life.

10:30.060 --> 10:47.065
So in other words, when someone in Alpha, when someone on a street corner, when someone over a coffee, when someone sharing over a barbecue, shares about the life, death, and resurrection of Jesus, the good news of Christ to a person, the Spirit of God is hovering over that spot.

10:47.085 --> 10:50.130
No matter if the person says yes or no to Christ,

10:50.210 --> 10:52.312
When you share the good news, you're not alone.

10:52.433 --> 10:56.397
It is a guaranteed place of encounter because the power of God is in the room.

10:57.699 --> 11:00.121
The second guaranteed place of encountering God is Scripture.

11:00.822 --> 11:06.609
The Bible, the Scriptures is a place where God always speaks.

11:06.629 --> 11:09.652
The Holy Spirit is always present, always overshadowing these words.

11:10.053 --> 11:14.738
Paul's summary of what Scripture is is found in 2 Timothy 3, 16.

11:15.074 --> 11:24.465
In 17, all scriptures God breathed, it's useful for teaching us, rebuking us, correcting us, training us in righteousness so the servant of God may be thoroughly equipped for every good work.

11:24.765 --> 11:28.910
The Holy Spirit's all was leading us and guiding us into God's truth.

11:29.310 --> 11:30.772
The holy faith passed down.

11:31.092 --> 11:32.734
Where's Jesus' teachings found?

11:32.994 --> 11:34.636
Where all of God's stories found?

11:34.736 --> 11:36.959
Where are God's thoughts and wants and desires?

11:37.239 --> 11:40.903
Where his revelations, his commands, his promises, his yeses and his nose?

11:41.264 --> 11:43.186
Where's the apostles' teaching found?

11:43.298 --> 11:46.122
in the Bible, in the Scriptures, in the written Word of God.

11:46.523 --> 11:48.105
This is God's inspired Word.

11:48.646 --> 11:52.572
The Holy Spirit leads us and teaches us because He's the author of Scripture.

11:53.073 --> 12:00.024
There might be 66 books in the Scriptures and multiple authors, but behind them there's actually one author.

12:00.785 --> 12:04.250
The Holy Spirit leads us, speaks to us, and forms us in the Bible.

12:04.290 --> 12:05.512
That's why He's called the Spirit of Truth.

12:05.532 --> 12:06.814
There's unity and diversity.

12:07.275 --> 12:09.599
And again, He's always hovering over the Scriptures.

12:09.639 --> 12:11.762
You cannot divorce the written Word of God,

12:12.290 --> 12:14.532
from the living word spirit.

12:15.033 --> 12:18.636
And by the way, you can't understand the Bible without its author.

12:19.397 --> 12:21.960
When you open the Bible, God speaks, it's guaranteed.

12:22.861 --> 12:24.282
The third place is spiritual disciplines.

12:24.302 --> 12:25.283
We talk about this all the time.

12:25.663 --> 12:31.910
Spiritual disciplines are the only ongoing place of transformation after you meet God through Jesus.

12:32.530 --> 12:36.294
Holy habits keep our relationship healthy, right, balanced.

12:36.434 --> 12:40.338
After you say yes, Jesus used these to walk with God the Father.

12:41.154 --> 12:47.002
So to be like Jesus, we must walk like Jesus did and share in his lifestyle.

12:47.563 --> 12:49.606
And they provide this dynamic experience.

12:49.626 --> 12:55.554
See, positionally, upstairs statically right now, you're a child of God, you're predestined, you're called, you're loved, you're forgiven.

12:55.574 --> 12:56.456
That's all true.

12:56.856 --> 13:01.403
And that's a static, unmovable truth, but it's also a dynamic relationship.

13:02.083 --> 13:08.693
So things like simplicity, confessing your sins to each other, praying, fasting, solitude, silence, studying God's Word.

13:08.713 --> 13:09.554
There's so many.

13:10.658 --> 13:15.632
You encounter him because he's among us and within you if you're a Christian.

13:16.635 --> 13:20.306
Now, the fourth area, we spend a lot of time in this church, having a spiritual gift.

13:20.930 --> 13:22.472
Why is this a guaranteed place of encounter?

13:22.532 --> 13:28.099
Well, spiritual gifts are the only ongoing guaranteed place of having given power to do God's work from.

13:28.560 --> 13:36.530
Jesus used them, and since we're the body of Christ, we're called together to use the same gifts to imitate and act like Jesus and be near Him.

13:37.091 --> 13:38.633
Gifts are related to doing.

13:38.653 --> 13:40.916
The fruit of the Spirit is about character.

13:41.417 --> 13:48.626
You and we will not have all 21 gifts personally, but we're all called individually to have the fruit of the Spirit.

13:48.994 --> 13:49.876
I share this all the time.

13:50.376 --> 14:01.676
What you're born with, natural gifts, you could be born athletic or born brilliant or do math really well, or you can learn things, amazing things like computer science or fill in the blank.

14:02.016 --> 14:09.269
Natural and learn things are good and amazing and can be used for God's kingdom, but you do not need the Holy Spirit to do those things.

14:09.970 --> 14:12.454
They're not guaranteed places of encounter and power.

14:13.536 --> 14:14.738
Scripture is clear though.

14:15.138 --> 14:16.459
1 Corinthians 12, 11.

14:16.900 --> 14:19.923
All these spiritual gifts are the work of the one and same Holy Spirit.

14:20.203 --> 14:23.146
The Holy Spirit distributes them to each one just as He determines.

14:23.546 --> 14:38.661
So the Holy Spirit's presence is guaranteed every time we use our God-given spiritual gifts because they're God-given places of service and He needs to be in the room for the, like He's the electricity for the electric car or He's the gas for the car.

14:38.741 --> 14:41.764
In other words, if you don't have Him, the gifts aren't even there.

14:42.264 --> 14:44.306
See, when you use a spiritual gift,

14:44.642 --> 14:49.413
You're accessing someone and someone's power that's not you, but still you're working with Him.

14:49.874 --> 14:50.495
It's guaranteed.

14:51.698 --> 14:54.764
Another guaranteed place of encounter is gathered worship.

14:55.426 --> 14:58.693
When we sing in community, we enter into God's holy presence.

14:59.314 --> 15:00.477
We join with all the angels.

15:00.537 --> 15:04.626
We enter actually into the environment where everyone who is loyal to Christ

15:05.026 --> 15:06.168
who's died is already there.

15:06.328 --> 15:07.950
My great-grandmother is there.

15:08.010 --> 15:09.232
My grandparents are there.

15:09.432 --> 15:10.033
Abraham's there.

15:10.113 --> 15:10.854
Moses is there.

15:10.934 --> 15:11.595
David's there.

15:11.915 --> 15:12.416
Fill in the blank.

15:12.496 --> 15:14.959
Paul and Timothy and Titus and Peter.

15:15.260 --> 15:20.026
And we walk into an environment, actually, that if we didn't have Jesus' covering, we would die.

15:21.087 --> 15:24.872
We're in that presence, if you're in a gathered site right now, right now.

15:25.954 --> 15:26.755
And let me ask this question.

15:26.815 --> 15:30.320
I'm going to talk about this a lot more today that I have in the past.

15:30.460 --> 15:35.026
Do you actually say that's true before you come to gathered worship?

15:35.618 --> 15:41.067
Right now this is happening, whether you feel it or not, see it or not, God is among us and we're in God's holy place.

15:41.107 --> 15:42.510
And the Bible teaches this, Psalm 22.

15:43.471 --> 15:47.538
God literally inhabits, sits among, sits in the praises of his people.

15:48.239 --> 15:50.643
James says, if you draw near to God, he draws near to you.

15:51.405 --> 15:55.732
Paul actually says that the Christian community is the literal temple of God.

15:56.954 --> 15:58.577
What did Jesus say in Matthew 18?

15:59.018 --> 16:01.682
Where two or three gathered my name, I am what?

16:01.826 --> 16:03.288
With them, that's not metaphor.

16:03.628 --> 16:04.690
That's not some fake promise.

16:04.730 --> 16:05.671
He's actually in the room.

16:05.911 --> 16:08.374
He's there by his spirit.

16:08.394 --> 16:11.778
So gathered worship is a guaranteed place of encounter.

16:12.880 --> 16:14.362
Another place is communion.

16:15.203 --> 16:20.169
Now, in this church, we don't believe Jesus is actually in the bread and the wine or the juice.

16:21.290 --> 16:24.815
But we also don't believe this is just remembering something that happened before.

16:26.236 --> 16:30.802
Churches call this communion or the Lord's supper or Eucharist or the Lord's table.

16:31.138 --> 16:33.120
Of course, it is a place of remembrance.

16:33.140 --> 16:37.246
It's where we stop and it says in 1 Corinthians 11, we proclaim Lord's death until He comes.

16:37.306 --> 16:41.911
Yes, we remember, we reflect on His death, His resurrection, we're thankful.

16:42.232 --> 16:44.835
We remember all that true, all that incredible truth.

16:44.895 --> 16:46.757
But it's not just remembrance.

16:47.659 --> 16:48.399
It's communion.

16:49.301 --> 16:50.822
Think about what the word means to commune.

16:50.842 --> 16:54.026
The commune means you actually are with others and with Him.

16:54.087 --> 16:58.212
Right from the beginning of scripture, it's not good that we're alone.

16:58.812 --> 17:00.114
We're not called to be alone.

17:00.546 --> 17:06.475
And this meal, no matter how it's served, is hosted by Jesus himself.

17:07.436 --> 17:09.199
The Jews and the bread are not Jesus.

17:09.219 --> 17:10.320
They don't turn in anything.

17:10.360 --> 17:11.823
They're symbols that focus our attention.

17:12.183 --> 17:12.824
Yes, yes, yes.

17:13.205 --> 17:22.759
But let me tell you, when you come up in a service to receive communion at a table, or it's passed, in that moment, Jesus is the one truly serving you.

17:23.860 --> 17:24.962
It's a place of forgiveness.

17:26.024 --> 17:27.666
It's a place where he can be encountered.

17:28.514 --> 17:33.860
And like I share every year, it's also a reminder that Jesus loves eating with sinners.

17:33.880 --> 17:34.220
Like us.

17:35.582 --> 17:37.864
Communion is a profound place of encounter.

17:38.986 --> 17:40.307
Then there's of course water baptism.

17:40.347 --> 17:45.132
Now we don't believe that you're saved through baptism or you get the Holy Spirit through baptism.

17:45.353 --> 17:45.613
No.

17:46.374 --> 17:52.460
But we do believe Jesus by the Holy Spirit is very close and very present every single time someone goes public with their faith.

17:53.061 --> 17:54.002
We say this all the time.

17:54.658 --> 17:57.681
Getting baptized, I say, this is my wedding ring.

17:57.821 --> 17:58.942
I've done this thousand times, right?

17:58.982 --> 17:59.783
This is my wedding ring.

18:00.504 --> 18:08.511
And this is a public declaration that I am off the market and I belong to my wife, Joanna, and she belongs to me.

18:09.072 --> 18:12.295
It's a public demonstration of an inward thing that we've already committed to.

18:12.695 --> 18:15.378
And we put this on or connect it to the vows.

18:15.418 --> 18:18.481
So when someone's baptized, they're making vows.

18:18.641 --> 18:23.666
Trust me, the groom is in the room when the vows are being said.

18:24.034 --> 18:31.966
So every time you're sitting in a service and you're watching someone getting baptized or you finally decided to obey Jesus and get baptized, he's right there.

18:32.647 --> 18:34.651
And of course he is because what did he say in Matthew 28?

18:34.751 --> 18:45.888
Go and make disciples of all ethnic groups, all nations, baptizing them in the name of God the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit, teaching them to obey everything I've commanded you and I'm with you always to the very end of the age.

18:47.350 --> 18:52.338
Now the last guaranteed place of encounter in scripture is suffering

18:53.186 --> 18:57.834
for the sake of the gospel, not just suffering in general, suffering for the sake of the gospel.

18:57.914 --> 18:59.857
Now, let me bring clarity to this call.

19:00.839 --> 19:03.804
Suffering has to be viewed on a sliding scale.

19:04.805 --> 19:07.570
Again, this week or the last month I've seen this online.

19:07.650 --> 19:12.238
So many Christians in the West say, oh my goodness, all we do is complain here.

19:12.298 --> 19:13.600
We're not really persecuted.

19:13.901 --> 19:15.403
We're not suffering like the rest of church.

19:15.423 --> 19:16.445
There's no persecution here.

19:16.465 --> 19:17.186
We're not suffering here.

19:17.206 --> 19:19.570
Well, actually that's not true.

19:20.354 --> 19:24.860
That's why we need to understand Christian suffering for the gospel again on a sliding scale.

19:25.421 --> 19:27.063
Now, here's the truth.

19:27.363 --> 19:34.232
One out of eight Christians, as I'm literally recording this message, is under direct persecution worldwide.

19:36.075 --> 19:37.196
They are in real trouble.

19:38.117 --> 19:45.347
Even in the last month, I have witnessed and watched multiple churches in one province, for example, in India, be burned to the ground.

19:45.928 --> 19:47.730
Two or three hundred Christians on the run

19:48.066 --> 19:51.091
sleeping outdoors, pastors assaulted.

19:51.211 --> 19:53.234
Like, this is real.

19:53.274 --> 20:00.104
Actually, there is more persecution against the church today than there has ever been in 2000 years.

20:01.306 --> 20:02.007
So that's true.

20:02.047 --> 20:03.789
That's real suffering for the gospel.

20:04.170 --> 20:15.006
And it's a guaranteed place of encounter, as we'll see, but actually, Open Doors, who is a global organization that evaluates Christian suffering, has the best definition, in my opinion, of persecution.

20:16.048 --> 20:17.650
Persecution or suffering

20:17.954 --> 20:23.842
and is any hostility experienced as a result of one's identification with Jesus.

20:24.903 --> 20:31.271
This includes hostile attitudes, words and actions, words, attitudes and actions towards Christians.

20:31.291 --> 20:45.810
So when you declare Jesus is the only way to heaven, when you say God is the Creator and is the final saying sexuality, when you choose not to lie or cheat and your boss has told you to do it and you lose access to a job, that's persecution.

20:46.562 --> 20:48.104
on a sliding scale, smaller.

20:48.745 --> 20:50.267
This does not apply to our political views.

20:51.048 --> 20:52.850
This does not apply when you're a jerk.

20:53.571 --> 20:57.536
This does not apply when you suffer because you do something wrong, like cheating in your taxes.

20:58.557 --> 21:10.452
But when you declare there's a heaven and a hell, when you gently declare with certainty that sincerity does not make you okay with God and does not actually change your life.

21:11.353 --> 21:15.378
When you stand up for the life of the unborn and the life of the elderly,

21:15.842 --> 21:26.534
When you actually declare that medical assisted suicide is murder, when you stand up for widows and orphans and immigrants in Jesus name, and you're rejected, it's small p persecution.

21:26.574 --> 21:40.690
So let me say this again, as orthodox, confessional, historic, biblically informed Christians, we will, I preach this all the time, we will always make the right and the left angry at the same time, because actually we belong to a different kingdom.

21:41.811 --> 21:44.114
We're pro-life and pro-immigrant in Jesus name.

21:45.026 --> 21:49.972
We actually believe in society and laws, but we also care for the marginalized.

21:50.673 --> 21:59.544
We boldly declare that Jesus is the Son of God and the only way to heaven, and yet we also would defend the civic right for anyone to believe anything they want.

22:00.865 --> 22:14.482
We as Christians actually know that God has asked us to conform ourselves to his understanding of sexuality and sexual life, but we at the same time will resist any violence in any form against anyone of any sexual orientation.

22:14.818 --> 22:16.520
Those categories don't fit in the world.

22:17.681 --> 22:22.105
And it really bothers the left and the right, but we're like, but we're with Jesus.

22:23.226 --> 22:24.647
So now most of us won't be beaten.

22:24.687 --> 22:32.315
Most of us, our church buildings won't be burned down, but we are in a moment in Canada where we have moved from apathy, you choose whatever you want.

22:32.395 --> 22:39.902
We're glad for you to hostility, the scriptures, Jesus and the claims of the Christian faith feel dangerous, inappropriate, and Canadian.

22:41.563 --> 22:44.306
No matter, not if, but when

22:45.058 --> 22:48.922
This happens to you by a boss or a friend or a family member or online.

22:49.442 --> 22:52.745
Don't hate that person, but pray for your enemies and rejoice.

22:53.966 --> 22:54.267
Why?

22:54.307 --> 23:09.681
Jesus said in Matthew 5, 11, blessed are you when people insult you, persecute you falsely, say lie, say all kinds of evil things against you, rejoice and be glad because great is your reward in heaven for in the same way they persecuted the prophets who were before you.

23:10.842 --> 23:14.866
See, suffering is worship, not a place to advance your rights.

23:16.066 --> 23:16.647
Here's the question.

23:16.667 --> 23:20.171
Are you willing to suffer in small and large ways for the sake of the kingdom?

23:20.951 --> 23:25.817
Have you made the connection between worship, suffering, and Jesus' unique presence?

23:25.837 --> 23:28.940
I mean, Paul says in Philippians 3, I want to know Christ.

23:29.080 --> 23:33.305
I want to know the power of his resurrection and participate in his sufferings.

23:34.046 --> 23:39.452
So when we suffer for the sake of the kingdom of God, we actually will encounter him.

23:39.532 --> 23:40.453
He is present.

23:40.713 --> 23:42.936
And by the way, I'm just going to go off script here for a minute too.

23:43.316 --> 23:45.138
I'd be remiss if I didn't do this.

23:45.858 --> 23:50.025
He's also uniquely present when we deny ourselves.

23:50.045 --> 24:01.885
See, our whole culture tells us that we will find life when we believe in ourselves, love ourselves, look inside of us, do inward journeys, write, manifest to you, fill in all the things.

24:01.905 --> 24:09.778
Listen, Jesus says we are called to crucify our flesh, deny who we are and what we want to be when he says no to those things.

24:10.082 --> 24:25.820
And when we actually say no to things that we want to do, that we feel we should do or actually feel we are, and we say no for Jesus, because we love Him more than these other loves, in that moment of suffering, it's worship, and Jesus is close.

24:27.422 --> 24:35.231
So the gospel, scripture, spiritual discipline, spiritual gifts, worship, communion, baptism, suffering for Jesus, salvation does not earn by these things.

24:36.072 --> 24:38.194
They don't get God's attention more.

24:38.722 --> 24:48.679
but they actually strengthen and give courage and the Holy Spirit is present and the Holy Spirit takes us in those environments that Jesus takes us to the Father and we of course get to be like Jesus.

24:48.739 --> 24:55.370
Now, there's one thing I say it all the time and a lot of people zone out, so actually find the mustard, find the mustard in the fridge.

24:57.374 --> 24:58.976
Our personal holiness matters.

25:00.399 --> 25:04.626
The power and the person you're meeting in those environments can be grieved.

25:05.986 --> 25:10.731
That's why multiple Christians can continually walk into these environments and never be changed.

25:12.093 --> 25:14.275
Paul put it best in Ephesians 4, 30.

25:14.836 --> 25:20.862
Don't grieve the Holy Spirit of God with whom you've been sealed for the day of redemption or to the day of redemption.

25:21.423 --> 25:26.408
So when we grieve the Holy Spirit, in other words, we just don't repent.

25:26.428 --> 25:26.989
We don't care.

25:27.209 --> 25:31.954
Listen, when we grieve the spirit, the spiritual gifts don't disappear, but they're power dims.

25:32.578 --> 25:42.069
When we grieve the Holy Spirit and we go to use spiritual disciplines or practices, they become powerless to transform because actually we're grieving the one we want to go here and listen to.

25:43.790 --> 25:48.556
In other words, don't grieve the one that you're trying to meet as you ring the doorbell to walk into that environment.

25:49.977 --> 25:51.339
Okay, so let me just do this real quick.

25:51.359 --> 25:52.300
We know what a disciple is.

25:53.221 --> 25:57.546
We know actually how to find our rabbi now in these environments.

25:58.547 --> 26:01.490
And so the question again is, how does this function on the ground?

26:02.306 --> 26:12.858
And so years ago, we took a lot of time to actually outline what discipleship looks like on the ground in this church community.

26:13.478 --> 26:15.080
So I'm going to go through this language again.

26:15.140 --> 26:22.869
We need to hear this and move forward together, one understanding, one common script, so we can become, of course, more fully devoted.

26:22.909 --> 26:31.538
Now, this is not just about common language, but it's actually also a way that I can genuinely evaluate myself and my disciple.

26:31.810 --> 26:32.831
Am I not a disciple?

26:33.372 --> 26:37.158
If I am a disciple, where am I on this journey?

26:37.318 --> 26:38.580
Where was I last September?

26:39.000 --> 26:40.362
Where was I last January?

26:40.662 --> 26:41.363
Where am I now?

26:41.544 --> 26:43.126
And make the needed connection.

26:43.346 --> 26:51.297
What we're going to talk about these, we call them discipleship dimensions here, are based on all the guaranteed places of encounter.

26:52.379 --> 26:54.943
So one is based on the other.

26:55.003 --> 27:00.210
So we say there are five discipleship dimensions that make us more fully devoted.

27:00.770 --> 27:02.272
The first one, well, let me just go to the most.

27:02.292 --> 27:06.998
Celebrate big, connect small, walk with Jesus, share the work, engage in mission.

27:07.058 --> 27:08.119
That's how we talk here.

27:08.880 --> 27:09.481
Celebrate big.

27:09.521 --> 27:13.145
We believe in celebrating God together in big gatherings.

27:13.405 --> 27:15.027
We see this right in the early church movement.

27:15.047 --> 27:17.290
We talked this event last week in mission and vision.

27:18.091 --> 27:19.072
They met in the temple courts.

27:19.092 --> 27:26.501
There was three, four, five thousand plus people at once gathering right within the first year of the church.

27:27.322 --> 27:30.226
So, like the early church, we rally,

27:30.498 --> 27:36.728
We are drawn to large gatherings where we hear preaching and teaching and we sing together and we pray together and we give together.

27:36.988 --> 27:38.030
We take communion together.

27:38.070 --> 27:39.793
We witness baptisms together.

27:40.193 --> 27:41.816
We serve in all sorts of ways.

27:41.856 --> 27:43.939
We pass on the faith to the next generation.

27:44.961 --> 27:46.383
God has called us to gather.

27:46.523 --> 27:47.785
Gathering is not optional.

27:48.366 --> 27:49.528
It is what we are.

27:50.670 --> 27:51.471
And why is it important?

27:51.491 --> 27:56.018
If you're going through a difficult season, an amazing season, if you're bored.

27:56.610 --> 28:01.816
We're called to celebrate the bigness and the goodness of our God regardless of circumstance.

28:02.837 --> 28:04.859
This is how we cling to promises in tough times.

28:04.879 --> 28:06.101
We thank Him for answered prayer.

28:06.421 --> 28:07.422
We celebrate big.

28:07.963 --> 28:11.266
Jesus is always with us when we gather.

28:11.286 --> 28:12.367
Second one is connect small.

28:12.468 --> 28:16.692
It's sort of the other side of the coin of celebrate big.

28:16.712 --> 28:18.314
We see this again in Acts 2, 46.

28:18.694 --> 28:20.056
They met together in the temple courts.

28:20.136 --> 28:20.937
There's the big gathering.

28:21.337 --> 28:22.499
They broke bread in their homes.

28:23.400 --> 28:24.080
Small gathering.

28:24.601 --> 28:25.522
They did life together.

28:25.602 --> 28:26.323
They ate together.

28:26.343 --> 28:26.823
They shared.

28:26.864 --> 28:27.284
They helped.

28:27.304 --> 28:29.587
They had close relationships with each other.

28:29.987 --> 28:31.489
The same is true for us as a sanctus.

28:31.569 --> 28:35.414
We believe in connecting small is equally as important as celebrating big.

28:35.534 --> 28:37.496
It's the primary place we do.

28:37.516 --> 28:40.740
This is connect groups, a place where someone knows where you are spiritually.

28:41.121 --> 28:42.763
When tough things happen, they're there for you.

28:43.143 --> 28:44.525
It's about authentic relationships.

28:44.565 --> 28:46.087
You unpack or walk with Jesus.

28:46.487 --> 28:47.949
How is the sermon affecting your life?

28:48.290 --> 28:49.631
You trust others to do the saying.

28:49.651 --> 28:50.012
You pray.

28:50.052 --> 28:50.412
You eat.

28:50.432 --> 28:50.773
You learn.

28:50.793 --> 28:51.233
You support.

28:51.273 --> 28:51.954
You care.

28:52.098 --> 28:54.140
And again, we do this because Jesus did this.

28:54.200 --> 28:56.743
Jesus spent so much of his time just with 12 people.

28:57.164 --> 29:05.874
Now, let me just take a moment and pause and just again, either clarify or give direction about this.

29:06.534 --> 29:16.426
Because of course, during COVID, some of us actually, many of us were in the system where we were in connect groups.

29:16.526 --> 29:20.370
And then suddenly, of course, we weren't in connect groups because of COVID.

29:20.802 --> 29:21.523
So a few things.

29:21.563 --> 29:31.136
Number one, there is alpha, where that's a great expression of connect groups, where you're actually sitting with others and learning and engaging about the Christian faith.

29:31.237 --> 29:33.400
And seekers and skeptics do this is amazing.

29:34.201 --> 29:37.185
Connect groups, though, can take many forms beyond alpha.

29:37.706 --> 29:43.514
So it can be a classic connect group where you're in a house and you've listened to sermon, you're talking through stuff, sure.

29:43.914 --> 29:46.578
It can be two or three of you gathering intentionally

29:46.786 --> 29:50.351
to pray with each other, talk to each other, maybe talk through the sermon together.

29:51.052 --> 29:54.196
Lots of us in our church are in different ages and stages.

29:54.236 --> 29:58.721
So some of us, this is not me so much anymore, we've got young kids and it's like chaos.

29:58.782 --> 30:03.488
And so I know all sorts of groups have got together, those who have children, those who don't.

30:03.828 --> 30:08.434
And what they tend to do is one group will meet one week and the rest are with the kids and vice versa.

30:08.962 --> 30:20.576
All we're saying to you is if you're gathering in a smaller way to pray with each other, find out where someone is spiritually, read scripture together, connect to the sermon in an intentional way and all sorts of other things.

30:21.016 --> 30:22.258
Just let us know you're doing it.

30:22.899 --> 30:29.867
That's actually the thing we need to know because actually there are so many people in small environments doing good things and we don't even know.

30:30.207 --> 30:32.770
And also we need to encourage you to do this again.

30:32.851 --> 30:35.794
In a church of thousands, we still need to meet together in a small way.

30:36.450 --> 30:39.555
So you've got connect big, you've got connect small, and then you've got walk with Jesus.

30:40.436 --> 30:43.862
We can see the early church, of course, devoting themselves to the apostles' teachings.

30:43.902 --> 30:51.554
So we as a church can provide connect groups and teaching and worship and serving opportunities, but we cannot ever force you to spend time with Jesus.

30:52.455 --> 30:55.360
We have to take personal responsibility for our own walk with Christ.

30:55.440 --> 31:01.429
So like I said, we believe in spiritual disciplines like reading scripture or prayer or meditation or solitude.

31:02.511 --> 31:04.594
These are guaranteed places, right?

31:04.802 --> 31:11.991
The ongoing rhythm between you and Jesus is key, reading your Bible, praying, listening, like Jesus did to the Father.

31:12.932 --> 31:21.022
When you regularly walk with Jesus through prioritized time, it will change your life because he'll be there.

31:21.283 --> 31:25.568
Now, it's not always amazing and drastic and, oh my goodness, but it's real.

31:26.789 --> 31:28.872
We want to encourage you to walk with Jesus personally.

31:28.912 --> 31:29.132
Why?

31:29.453 --> 31:33.618
Because if you notice, Jesus spent a lot of time walking

31:33.762 --> 31:34.784
personally with His Father.

31:36.246 --> 31:37.047
So we gather big.

31:37.167 --> 31:37.848
Jesus did that.

31:38.429 --> 31:39.130
We gather small.

31:39.210 --> 31:39.931
Jesus did that.

31:40.993 --> 31:42.856
We spend time alone with God.

31:42.896 --> 31:43.597
Jesus did that.

31:44.378 --> 31:45.320
Oh, and then we share the work.

31:46.101 --> 31:51.709
Again, like I said, let me say this again, we know the Scriptures teach that every Christian has at least one spiritual gift.

31:52.591 --> 31:57.458
And since these are given by the Spirit to you, we are commanded to use them.

31:58.018 --> 31:59.340
You'll get immense joy from this.

31:59.480 --> 32:07.371
We've always seen this burnout rates drop in ministries much of the time because you start accessing a power that's beyond natural or acquired gifts.

32:08.673 --> 32:11.637
And also this avoids and breaks down comparison.

32:12.758 --> 32:13.579
I don't have to be like you.

32:13.599 --> 32:14.520
You don't have to be like me.

32:14.801 --> 32:16.403
We get joyful and we serve God.

32:17.084 --> 32:19.167
This is not about independence or dependence.

32:19.207 --> 32:20.068
It's interdependence.

32:21.069 --> 32:21.630
Why do we do this?

32:21.690 --> 32:27.378
Well, because Jesus actually used spiritual gifts to change the world, to do ministry from.

32:27.906 --> 32:29.568
We have to also choose to serve.

32:29.968 --> 32:31.810
And we serve in our gifts.

32:31.830 --> 32:35.334
And also, of course, there are times when we have to serve beyond our gifts.

32:35.454 --> 32:38.778
And that just becomes duty and discipline because we love Jesus.

32:40.139 --> 32:41.601
The last one is engage in mission.

32:43.122 --> 32:49.549
What we see in Jesus' life and in the early church's life is like outlandish generosity, actually.

32:50.691 --> 32:53.734
And we talk about engage in mission in two directions.

32:53.814 --> 32:55.476
We talk about it with the gospel.

32:55.876 --> 32:57.458
We talk about it with finances.

32:58.018 --> 33:05.292
We're called to take the gospel to good news, the life, death, and resurrection story right to our families, workplaces, neighborhoods, and friends.

33:06.153 --> 33:10.722
We're called to give time and money also to invest in things at last.

33:11.524 --> 33:15.190
Generosity is always the mark of a fully devoted follower of Jesus.

33:15.351 --> 33:19.218
Generosity is always the mark of a fully devoted follower of Jesus.

33:19.906 --> 33:36.442
And so sharing the gospel and giving the good news by inviting someone to Alpha or just sitting over a beer and sharing, oh my goodness, let me tell you how Jesus changed my life or sitting with that neighbor or friend and building a relationship in time, sharing how the life and death and resurrection of Jesus has changed you.

33:36.902 --> 33:42.187
That is this dynamic, this environment, but so is giving.

33:42.988 --> 33:49.554
And actually, I know sometimes in church it's weird to talk about giving, but actually its heart is

33:49.666 --> 33:51.548
about loving God and loving each other.

33:51.768 --> 33:56.253
And so we're called to give regularly, unashamedly, by the way, to our local church.

33:56.634 --> 34:01.459
And then the reason why we have local and global partners is because we realize we're not the only thing that God cares about.

34:01.779 --> 34:09.047
And so when you give here, so we get to do what we're called to do here under God's direction, we get to bless local communities and global communities.

34:09.128 --> 34:13.973
Engaging in mission through Jesus, you'll begin to love people you've never loved before.

34:14.654 --> 34:18.578
Giving financially, make sure that materialism

34:18.978 --> 34:26.868
and also fear doesn't win your heart and sharing the good news and partnering local and globally, just what we're called to do.

34:27.028 --> 34:29.571
Now, those are the dimensions.

34:30.332 --> 34:31.874
Don't misunderstand what I just went through.

34:32.235 --> 34:38.142
You can almost take this wrong and go, well, here's my checklist and like, click, click, click, click, click, click, click, click.

34:38.162 --> 34:41.266
But number one, this is love that moves to action.

34:41.746 --> 34:42.367
It's about love.

34:43.068 --> 34:44.690
And this is more like a continuum.

34:46.146 --> 34:53.053
Now, I understand, and we, of course, all understand, that you can't do all of these all the time at every moment.

34:54.014 --> 34:58.919
But let me give two very simple, direct ways we can respond to this.

34:59.279 --> 35:04.585
Whether we've heard this literally what I've done for 20 years, or this is the first time you're hearing it, one.

35:04.645 --> 35:13.554
And if I can especially ask all of you who've been part of this church for a long time, I'm now begging your attention.

35:14.370 --> 35:15.832
Pickering, Bowmanville, right?

35:16.212 --> 35:17.474
Ajax, some of you online.

35:17.494 --> 35:18.495
You've been here for a while.

35:18.515 --> 35:27.405
So, we're the ones who've been for the long run, and we, much of the time, are called to set the trend of what is and what's not.

35:28.566 --> 35:33.292
Can I ask our whole church to choose to change our expectations again?

35:33.752 --> 35:35.935
Because we did in the past, and I think we've lost it now.

35:37.016 --> 35:42.002
When you're about to take communion, when you're about to witness a baptism, or you're finally about to obey,

35:43.074 --> 36:11.250
When you're gathering and you're singing to the Father, the Son, and the Spirit, when you're serving and releasing prayer and using discernment or faith or miracles, when you're greeting at that door or making coffee using that gift of serving, when actually you are teaching that kid in Sanctus Kids or in a junior high context, that Bible story, when two of three of you are gathering, talking about the sermon and praying in that Starbucks, do you actually

36:11.426 --> 36:15.892
say out loud or just before that, this is a guaranteed place of meeting.

36:17.253 --> 36:26.385
Again, this does not mean every time that we walk into these environments, it's so life-changing and overwhelming and so powerful and emotional and Gabriel showed up and fire from heaven.

36:26.485 --> 36:28.247
No, no, no, but here's the question.

36:28.327 --> 36:37.518
Do you say I am about to encounter the living God, no matter who's preaching, no matter what the results are, no matter who's leading worship, no matter, I feel him, he's here.

36:38.560 --> 36:40.402
This, I mentioned this a few weeks ago,

36:41.410 --> 36:45.596
This is not about us getting hyped up again post COVID to get back into church.

36:45.616 --> 36:46.257
It's not about hype.

36:47.479 --> 36:49.522
It's not even about being excited sometimes.

36:50.784 --> 36:52.306
It's about expectation.

36:55.331 --> 37:08.370
I remember when I first taught this in our church, the spiritual dynamic of our church changed overnight because people started coming to services and realized, like really realized,

37:08.578 --> 37:10.201
that God inhabits the praises of the people.

37:10.562 --> 37:12.866
Really realized Jesus was about to serve the communion.

37:13.307 --> 37:14.469
Like, it changed.

37:14.509 --> 37:15.551
So here's my encouragement.

37:16.233 --> 37:20.341
Can you start as you're driving to church and preparing to go serve somewhere, go to a connect group?

37:20.401 --> 37:23.166
Just say out loud, I'm about to encounter the living God.

37:24.489 --> 37:31.442
And start actually changing the atmosphere of our church, the expectation of our church to something that is guaranteed.

37:32.610 --> 37:45.529
Because if we all come expectant, even though we're tired, all come expectant, even though we're distracted, all come expected, even though we had a bad or great week last week, when we come expectant, the atmosphere of faith in the truest sense does change.

37:47.392 --> 37:48.013
Here's the other thing.

37:48.654 --> 37:55.664
Commit to at least two of these discipleship dimensions this year and make them real, calendarized, and a priority.

37:56.385 --> 38:02.514
Like really give your life to them and walk with Jesus in them and walk with each other in them.

38:03.522 --> 38:10.569
If our whole church did that, not only with expectation changing, there would be a massive shift.

38:11.670 --> 38:19.097
So Lord, would you lead our friends across the church who don't know you yet to encounter you, to become a disciple?

38:19.117 --> 38:22.920
And for we who are disciples begin to change our expectations.

38:23.741 --> 38:33.490
And now Father and Son, send the Spirit and speak to us directly right now about the two or three areas you are inviting and probably commanding us

38:33.954 --> 38:35.137
to actually participate in.

38:35.158 --> 38:37.905
Would you speak and then would we be quick to obey?

38:38.186 --> 38:40.393
This is what we pray in Jesus' name.

38:40.774 --> 38:43.602
And we all said together, amen.

